00:19:09.080 --> 00:19:11.080
So what's the message of that?

00:19:11.080 --> 00:19:12.380
The message is--

00:19:12.380 --> 00:19:14.930
we've talked about what we
perceive, what we see by

00:19:14.930 --> 00:19:16.650
expectations in context.

00:19:16.650 --> 00:19:19.860
But it's also we have very
limited what psychologists

00:19:19.860 --> 00:19:21.310
call attentional resources.

00:19:21.310 --> 00:19:23.960
We can pay attention
to a limited number

00:19:23.960 --> 00:19:25.240
of things at a time.

00:19:25.240 --> 00:19:28.040
And even when those things can
be right in front of us, if

00:19:28.040 --> 00:19:31.170
our attention is focused or
occupied by something else,

00:19:31.170 --> 00:19:34.400
like counting the passes
in a difficult scene--

00:19:34.400 --> 00:19:38.060
it wouldn't work if there was
one or two passes only,

00:19:38.060 --> 00:19:39.400
because you would notice it.

00:19:39.400 --> 00:19:42.610
But when your mind is focused on
identifying all the passes

00:19:42.610 --> 00:19:44.065
among the players-- and the
white shirts are moving,

00:19:44.065 --> 00:19:47.360
they're weaving with the other
players and so on--

00:19:47.360 --> 00:19:50.920
then your attention is absorbed
by that, and some of

00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:53.390
it is not left over to notice
what's right in front of you.

00:19:53.390 --> 00:19:54.750
And we'll talk more
about that.

00:19:54.750 --> 00:19:57.650
But it's a huge thing with
humans that we can pay

00:19:57.650 --> 00:20:00.550
attention pretty well, on
average, to a thing at a time

00:20:00.550 --> 00:20:01.980
under many circumstances.

00:20:01.980 --> 00:20:05.340
And the other things escape us
completely, even if they're

00:20:05.340 --> 00:20:07.830
obviously present if we were
looking at them or paying

00:20:07.830 --> 00:20:09.470
attention to them.

00:20:09.470 --> 00:20:13.490
So here's another example of how
our minds make our world--

00:20:13.490 --> 00:20:15.880
what we see and what we don't
see, what we pay attention to

00:20:15.880 --> 00:20:17.710
and what we don't pay
attention to.

00:20:17.710 --> 00:20:20.695
And that's something to
do with how we hear.

00:20:31.740 --> 00:20:33.330
OK, so I'm going
