00:21:33.220 --> 00:21:37.010
But the basic idea is most
people think they hear the

00:21:37.010 --> 00:21:40.160
word "da" coming from
the speaker.

00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:42.840
And in fact, in their mind they
do because that's how

00:21:42.840 --> 00:21:44.530
they interpret what
they're hearing.

00:21:44.530 --> 00:21:47.910
But in reality, the film clip
is a film clip of the person

00:21:47.910 --> 00:21:53.120
saying "ba ba ba." And then an
audio recording of the person

00:21:53.120 --> 00:21:58.650
saying "ga ga ga." Your mind
intertwines across modalities

00:21:58.650 --> 00:22:02.380
what you hear and what you see,
integrates them in some

00:22:02.380 --> 00:22:03.820
way below your level
of consciousness.

00:22:03.820 --> 00:22:05.510
You're not thinking about it.

00:22:05.510 --> 00:22:07.690
And you come up with a different
interpretation of

00:22:07.690 --> 00:22:09.370
what you hear.

00:22:09.370 --> 00:22:09.880
Right?

00:22:09.880 --> 00:22:12.130
So what you see would
be this one thing.

00:22:12.130 --> 00:22:13.240
What you hear is
another thing.

00:22:13.240 --> 00:22:16.200
When your eyes are open and your
ears are open, they meld

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:17.660
together and produce
something--

00:22:17.660 --> 00:22:19.250
a third thing that's
entirely different.

00:22:19.250 --> 00:22:23.100
Again, your mind interpreted
what you hear, not your ear

00:22:23.100 --> 00:22:26.380
interpreting what you hear,
in a simple sense.

00:22:26.380 --> 00:22:27.390
OK.

00:22:27.390 --> 00:22:29.520
How about things that we know?

00:22:29.520 --> 00:22:30.910
So let's think about this.

00:22:30.910 --> 00:22:34.020
If somebody were to ask you
which is farther east, closer

00:22:34.020 --> 00:22:35.840
to the Atlantic--

00:22:35.840 --> 00:22:40.210
San Diego, California,
or Reno, Nevada?

00:22:40.210 --> 00:22:43.330
Who likes San Diego as
being farther east?

00:22:43.330 --> 00:22:44.190
A few hands.

00:22:44.190 --> 00:22:46.470
Who likes Reno as being
farther east?

00:22:46.470 --> 00:22:47.350
OK.

00:22:47.350 --> 00:22:52.680
So, here's the mental map most
people have-- the mental map--

00:22:52.680 --> 00:22:56.320
which is we know California's
right next to the ocean with

00:22:56.320 --> 00:22:58.760
Arnold Schwarzenegger protecting
us on that side of

00:22:58.760 --> 00:23:00.800
the country, right?

00:23:00.800 --> 00:23:05.020
And then Nevada's a little bit
more towards Boston, right?

00:23:05.020 --> 00:23:05.570
OK.

00:23:05.570 --> 00:23:07.280
That's a mental map that
most people have.

00:23:07.280 --> 00:23:08.330
And that's how the
hands went up.

00:23:08.330 --> 00:23:09.870
This is the actual map.

00:23:09.870 --> 00:23:13.440
And the only actual map you've
ever seen, ever-- on a globe,

00:23:13.440 --> 00:23:14.680
on a map, anything.

00:23:14.680 --> 00:23:18.340
Because California takes a big
turn on the south, San Diego's

00:23:18.340 --> 00:23:20.890
further east than Reno.

00:23:20.890 --> 00:23:25.610
Why do we imagine, and most
people do, that Reno is

00:23:25.610 --> 00:23:31.000
further east, when you've never
seen a map or globe

00:23:31.000 --> 00:23:31.700
that's shown you that?

00:23:31.700 --> 00:23:34.490
Never ever, ever.

00:23:34.490 --> 00:23:35.740
Yeah.

00:23:38.050 --> 00:23:40.040
PROFESSOR: Because it's farther
from the ocean,

00:23:40.040 --> 00:23:43.120
because in our mind we go,
California's way out there.

00:23:43.120 --> 00:23:44.240
There's nothing--

00:23:44.240 --> 00:23:47.840
Hawaii is the only one out there
further west, right?

00:23:47.840 --> 00:23:51.480
So our mind makes this
answer despite that.

00:23:51.480 --> 00:23:53.610
And that's what we think
we might know.

00:23:53.610 --> 00:23:54.990
Now, we might not be
totally certain.

00:23:54.990 --> 00:23:57.960
We might not bet the
farm on that.

00:23:57.960 --> 00:23:59.360
Which is farther north--

00:23:59.360 --> 00:24:01.820
Philadelphia, Pennsylvania,
or Rome, Italy?

00:24:01.820 --> 00:24:03.600
So start to think-- how would
you think about that?

00:24:03.600 --> 00:24:04.610
It's not something you know.

00:24:04.610 --> 00:24:06.000
Nobody memorizes it, right?

00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:08.200
But how would you begin
to think which is

00:24:08.200 --> 00:24:10.300
probably more northern?

00:24:10.300 --> 00:24:11.020
What's your first gut?

00:24:11.020 --> 00:24:15.210
How many people like
Philadelphia being more north?

00:24:15.210 --> 00:24:16.740
How many people like Rome
being more north?

00:24:16.740 --> 00:24:19.210
There's kind of a mixture
of hands.

00:24:19.210 --> 00:24:25.650
The answer is that Rome is
north of Philadelphia.

00:24:25.650 --> 00:24:28.510
Mostly people will answer that
Philadelphia is north.

00:24:28.510 --> 00:24:31.830
Why they do that is they think
the US and Europe, they're

00:24:31.830 --> 00:24:34.420
both sort of above the equator,
below Antarctica,

00:24:34.420 --> 00:24:38.430
kind of a aligned, even
historically, culturally.

00:24:38.430 --> 00:24:40.840
So they think, well, Rome is
pretty south in Europe.

00:24:40.840 --> 00:24:41.220
And it is.

00:24:41.220 --> 00:24:42.240
It's in Italy.

00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:44.440
Philadelphia's reasonably
north in the US.

00:24:44.440 --> 00:24:46.230
It gets winters and all
that kinds of stuff.

00:24:46.230 --> 00:24:50.190
So a northern city in the US
has got to be north of a

00:24:50.190 --> 00:24:51.840
southern city in Europe.

00:24:51.840 --> 00:24:54.680
But in fact, Europe is-- the
whole continent is shifted up

00:24:54.680 --> 00:24:56.270
compared to the US.

00:24:56.270 --> 00:24:58.720
So you won't-- wait until get
